The paper deals with the synthesis of schedulers in Markov decision processes, which is a classic problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem is inspired by an electric-vehicle charging problem, which suggests a systems and control (cs.SY) perspective. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which are commonly studied in machine learning (cs.LG) and operations research (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with probabilistic models, which are studied in probability (cs.PR) and mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
